abstract: The reconstruction of call between the two leaders becomes a flash point in the evolving fight over impeachment.
snippet: The reconstruction of call between the two leaders becomes a flash point in the evolving fight over impeachment.
lead_paragraph: President Trump repeatedly pressured Ukraine’s leader to investigate leading Democrats as “a favor” to him during a telephone call last summer in which the two discussed the former Soviet republic’s need for more American financial aid to counter Russian aggression.

abstract: The American and British leaders meet their nemesis. It’s called the law.
snippet: The American and British leaders meet their nemesis. It’s called the law.
lead_paragraph: To see them together in New York, the two charlatans, after all their nationalist-revival shenanigans, encountering the quiet force of the law was an exquisite thing. I am not sure I have ever experienced Schadenfreude in purer form.

headline_main: Trump and Johnson on the Brink

abstract: It is far worse than we could have imagined.
snippet: It is far worse than we could have imagined.
lead_paragraph: Facing growing momentum behind a full House impeachment inquiry, President Trump evidently concluded that releasing a memorandum of his phone call on July 25 with President Volodymyr Zelensky of Ukraine would quiet the investigative fervor. He could not have been more wrong.

headline_main: Trump Has Just One Plan for Victory

abstract: The president and the Democrats may be girding for a constitutional clash, but their campaigns are working to capitalize on the moment with fund-raising appeals.
snippet: The president and the Democrats may be girding for a constitutional clash, but their campaigns are working to capitalize on the moment with fund-raising appeals.
lead_paragraph: The breathless text message from President Trump and his campaign landed soon after Speaker Nancy Pelosi announced a formal impeachment inquiry: “I need you on my Impeachment Defense Team.”

headline_main: Trump and 2020 Democrats Agree: Impeachment Fight Is a Chance to Rake In Cash

abstract: Wary of the way Republicans and President Trump attacked Hillary Clinton in 2016, the Biden camp is looking for ways to control the story line.
snippet: Wary of the way Republicans and President Trump attacked Hillary Clinton in 2016, the Biden camp is looking for ways to control the story line.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When a reporter asked former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Saturday if he had spoken to his son Hunter about his work in Ukraine, Mr. Biden jabbed his finger repeatedly at the reporter and shot back: “Ask the right questions.”

abstract: The Times’s Washington reporters are available to answer readers’ questions about the impeachment inquiry.
snippet: The Times’s Washington reporters are available to answer readers’ questions about the impeachment inquiry.
lead_paragraph: When Speaker Nancy Pelosi announced Tuesday that the House would launch a formal impeachment inquiry against President Trump and whether he enlisted a foreign power to help his political aims, she initiated a constitutional showdown without a certain outcome that will likely consume Washington for months to come.

headline_main: The Impeachment Process Is Complicated. Ask Our Reporters Your Questions.

abstract: Across the Democratic field, candidates are approaching the impeachment battle as a necessary process, but perhaps not one that ought to redefine their own campaigns.
snippet: Across the Democratic field, candidates are approaching the impeachment battle as a necessary process, but perhaps not one that ought to redefine their own campaigns.
lead_paragraph: KEENE, N.H. — Senator Elizabeth Warren’s message on impeachment was blunt and brief. On a college campus here, Ms. Warren reminded a crowd of hundreds that she had called for President Trump’s impeachment last spring, after the release of Robert S. Mueller III’s report on Russian interference in the 2016 election. Taking action against Mr. Trump, she said then, was “a matter of constitutional responsibility.”
